`mongodbatlas.Project` provides a Project resource. This allows project to be created.

> **IMPORTANT WARNING:**  Changing the name of an existing Project in your configuration will result the destruction of that Project and related resources (including Clusters) and the re-creation of those resources.  The provider will inform you of the destroyed/created resources before applying so be sure to verify any change to your environment before applying.

{{% examples %}}
## Example Usage

{{< chooser language "typescript,python,go,csharp" / >}}

{{% example csharp %}}
```csharp
using Pulumi;
using Mongodbatlas = Pulumi.Mongodbatlas;

class MyStack : Stack
{
    public MyStack()
    {
        var test = new Mongodbatlas.Project("test", new Mongodbatlas.ProjectArgs
        {
            OrgId = "<ORG_ID>",
            Teams = 
            {
                new Mongodbatlas.Inputs.ProjectTeamArgs
                {
                    RoleNames = 
                    {
                        "GROUP_OWNER",
                    },
                    TeamId = "5e0fa8c99ccf641c722fe645",
                },
                new Mongodbatlas.Inputs.ProjectTeamArgs
                {
                    RoleNames = 
                    {
                        "GROUP_READ_ONLY",
                        "GROUP_DATA_ACCESS_READ_WRITE",
                    },
                    TeamId = "5e1dd7b4f2a30ba80a70cd4rw",
                },
            },
        });
    }

}
```

package main

import (
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi-mongodbatlas/sdk/go/mongodbatlas"
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi/sdk/v2/go/pulumi"
)

func main() {
	pulumi.Run(func(ctx *pulumi.Context) error {
		_, err := mongodbatlas.NewProject(ctx, "test", &mongodbatlas.ProjectArgs{
			OrgId: pulumi.String("<ORG_ID>"),
			Teams: mongodbatlas.ProjectTeamArray{
				&mongodbatlas.ProjectTeamArgs{
					RoleNames: pulumi.StringArray{
						pulumi.String("GROUP_OWNER"),
					},
					TeamId: pulumi.String("5e0fa8c99ccf641c722fe645"),
				},
				&mongodbatlas.ProjectTeamArgs{
					RoleNames: pulumi.StringArray{
						pulumi.String("GROUP_READ_ONLY"),
						pulumi.String("GROUP_DATA_ACCESS_READ_WRITE"),
					},
					TeamId: pulumi.String("5e1dd7b4f2a30ba80a70cd4rw"),
				},
			},
		})
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		return nil
	})
}

## Supporting Types


<h4 id="projectteam">Project<wbr>Team</h4>
{{% choosable language nodejs %}}
> See the <a href="/docs/reference/pkg/nodejs/pulumi/mongodbatlas/types/input/#ProjectTeam">input</a> and <a href="/docs/reference/pkg/nodejs/pulumi/mongodbatlas/types/output/#ProjectTeam">output</a> API doc for this type.
{{% /choosable %}}

{{% choosable language go %}}
> See the <a href="https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/pulumi/pulumi-mongodbatlas/sdk/go/mongodbatlas/?tab=doc#ProjectTeamArgs">input</a> and <a href="https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/pulumi/pulumi-mongodbatlas/sdk/go/mongodbatlas/?tab=doc#ProjectTeamOutput">output</a> API doc for this type.
{{% /choosable %}}
{{% choosable language csharp %}}
> See the <a href="/docs/reference/pkg/dotnet/Pulumi.Mongodbatlas/Pulumi.Mongodbatlas.Inputs.ProjectTeamArgs.html">input</a> and <a href="/docs/reference/pkg/dotnet/Pulumi.Mongodbatlas/Pulumi.Mongodbatlas.Outputs.ProjectTeam.html">output</a> API doc for this type.
{{% /choosable %}}




{{% choosable language csharp %}}
<dl class="resources-properties">

    <dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="rolenames_csharp">
<a href="#rolenames_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Role<wbr>Names</a>
</span> 
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type"><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/csharp/language-reference/builtin-types/built-in-types">List&lt;string&gt;</a></span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}Each string in the array represents a project role you want to assign to the team. Every user associated with the team inherits these roles. You must specify an array even if you are only associating a single role with the team.
The following are valid roles:
* `GROUP_OWNER`
* `GROUP_READ_ONLY`
* `GROUP_DATA_ACCESS_ADMIN`
* `GROUP_DATA_ACCESS_READ_WRITE`
* `GROUP_DATA_ACCESS_READ_ONLY`
* `GROUP_CLUSTER_MANAGER`
{{% /md %}}</dd>

    <dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="teamid_csharp">
<a href="#teamid_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Team<wbr>Id</a>
</span> 
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type"><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/csharp/language-reference/builtin-types/built-in-types">string</a></span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The unique identifier of the team you want to associate with the project. The team and project must share the same parent organization.
{{% /md %}}</dd>

</dl>
{{% /choosable %}}


{{% choosable language go %}}
<dl class="resources-properties">

    <dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="rolenames_go">
<a href="#rolenames_go" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Role<wbr>Names</a>
</span> 
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type"><a href="https://golang.org/pkg/builtin/#string">[]string</a></span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}Each string in the array represents a project role you want to assign to the team. Every user associated with the team inherits these roles. You must specify an array even if you are only associating a single role with the team.
The following are valid roles:
* `GROUP_OWNER`
* `GROUP_READ_ONLY`
* `GROUP_DATA_ACCESS_ADMIN`

{{% /md %}}</dd>

{{% choosable language nodejs %}}
<dl class="resources-properties">

    <dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="rolenames_nodejs">

</span> 
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type"><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/string">string[]</a></span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}Each string in the array represents a project role you want to assign to the team. Every user associated with the team inherits these roles. You must specify an array even if you are only associating a single role with the team.
The following are valid roles:
* `GROUP_OWNER`
* `GROUP_READ_ONLY`
* `GROUP_DATA_ACCESS_ADMIN`
* `GROUP_DATA_ACCESS_READ_WRITE`
* `GROUP_DATA_ACCESS_READ_ONLY`
* `GROUP_CLUSTER_MANAGER`
{{% /md %}}</dd>

    <dt class="property-required"

    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The unique identifier of the team you want to associate with the project. The team and project must share the same parent organization.
{{% /md %}}</dd>

</dl>
